{"schema": {"fields":[{"type":"integer","name":"index"},{"type":"string","name":"author_association"},{"type":"string","name":"body"},{"type":"datetime","name":"created_at"},{"type":"string","name":"html_url"},{"type":"integer","name":"id"},{"type":"string","name":"issue_url"},{"type":"string","name":"node_id"},{"type":"datetime","name":"updated_at"},{"type":"string","name":"url"},{"type":"string","name":"user"}],"pandas_version":"0.20.0","primaryKey":["index"]}, "data": [{"index":0,"author_association":"OWNER","body":"Do you mind sharing some images that illustrate what you're trying to achieve?","created_at":"2017-06-26T23:18:50.000Z","html_url":"https:\/\/github.com\/mrdoob\/three.js\/issues\/11616#issuecomment-311208342","id":311208342,"issue_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/repos\/mrdoob\/three.js\/issues\/11616","node_id":"MDEyOklzc3VlQ29tbWVudDMxMTIwODM0Mg==","updated_at":"2017-06-26T23:18:50.000Z","url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/repos\/mrdoob\/three.js\/issues\/comments\/311208342","user":{"following_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/mrdoob\/following{\/other_user}","events_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/mrdoob\/events{\/privacy}","avatar_url":"https:\/\/avatars0.githubusercontent.com\/u\/97088?v=4","url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/mrdoob","gists_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/mrdoob\/gists{\/gist_id}","html_url":"https:\/\/github.com\/mrdoob","subscriptions_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/mrdoob\/subscriptions","node_id":"MDQ6VXNlcjk3MDg4","repos_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/mrdoob\/repos","received_events_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/mrdoob\/received_events","gravatar_id":"","starred_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/mrdoob\/starred{\/owner}{\/repo}","site_admin":false,"login":"mrdoob","type":"User","id":97088,"followers_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/mrdoob\/followers","organizations_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/mrdoob\/orgs"}},{"index":1,"author_association":"NONE","body":"Re @mrdoob, here is a case scenario, where in the first picture the shadows are driven by directional lighting and the objects color is affected. In the second picture, I remove the directional light (0 intensity) I get the proper colors, but I loose the shadows. I wish to have the shadows from the first picture with the lightning (object colors) from the second picture.\r\n\r\n![lightshadowissue](https:\/\/user-images.githubusercontent.com\/11213220\/27572488-9979c8ce-5b0c-11e7-85f1-1d76a125da6c.png)\r\n\r\n","created_at":"2017-06-27T05:53:57.000Z","html_url":"https:\/\/github.com\/mrdoob\/three.js\/issues\/11616#issuecomment-311260280","id":311260280,"issue_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/repos\/mrdoob\/three.js\/issues\/11616","node_id":"MDEyOklzc3VlQ29tbWVudDMxMTI2MDI4MA==","updated_at":"2017-06-27T05:53:57.000Z","url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/repos\/mrdoob\/three.js\/issues\/comments\/311260280","user":{"following_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/j3zusla\/following{\/other_user}","events_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/j3zusla\/events{\/privacy}","avatar_url":"https:\/\/avatars0.githubusercontent.com\/u\/11213220?v=4","url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/j3zusla","gists_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/j3zusla\/gists{\/gist_id}","html_url":"https:\/\/github.com\/j3zusla","subscriptions_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/j3zusla\/subscriptions","node_id":"MDQ6VXNlcjExMjEzMjIw","repos_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/j3zusla\/repos","received_events_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/j3zusla\/received_events","gravatar_id":"","starred_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/j3zusla\/starred{\/owner}{\/repo}","site_admin":false,"login":"j3zusla","type":"User","id":11213220,"followers_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/j3zusla\/followers","organizations_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/j3zusla\/orgs"}},{"index":2,"author_association":"COLLABORATOR","body":">the shadowmap shadows intensity is proportional to the light intensity property.\r\n\r\nIn three.js, shadows are the absence of light. The light intensity does not change the color of the shadow itself -- only the color of the surrounding illuminated area. You can see that in the images you posted.\r\n\r\nTry [ShadowMaterial](https:\/\/threejs.org\/docs\/#api\/materials\/ShadowMaterial). There are several examples of its use in the three.js examples.\r\n","created_at":"2017-06-27T14:53:35.000Z","html_url":"https:\/\/github.com\/mrdoob\/three.js\/issues\/11616#issuecomment-311383768","id":311383768,"issue_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/repos\/mrdoob\/three.js\/issues\/11616","node_id":"MDEyOklzc3VlQ29tbWVudDMxMTM4Mzc2OA==","updated_at":"2017-06-27T14:53:35.000Z","url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/repos\/mrdoob\/three.js\/issues\/comments\/311383768","user":{"following_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/WestLangley\/following{\/other_user}","events_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/WestLangley\/events{\/privacy}","avatar_url":"https:\/\/avatars2.githubusercontent.com\/u\/1000017?v=4","url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/WestLangley","gists_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/WestLangley\/gists{\/gist_id}","html_url":"https:\/\/github.com\/WestLangley","subscriptions_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/WestLangley\/subscriptions","node_id":"MDQ6VXNlcjEwMDAwMTc=","repos_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/WestLangley\/repos","received_events_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/WestLangley\/received_events","gravatar_id":"","starred_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/WestLangley\/starred{\/owner}{\/repo}","site_admin":false,"login":"WestLangley","type":"User","id":1000017,"followers_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/WestLangley\/followers","organizations_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/WestLangley\/orgs"}},{"index":3,"author_association":"NONE","body":"> only the color of the surrounding illuminated area \r\n\r\nYes, it is the effect that will be very useful to control (on\/off), specially when rendering shadows that simulate the outdoors. Indoors, one can getby using multiple light sources and shadows that affect its surrounding. On the other hand, when simulating outdoors, if there are multiple light sources, one can easely see that something is not right...\r\n\r\nThe ShadowMaterial from what I understand is to render shadows only. I was hoping to not have to use it as I have just migrated all the object materials to MeshStandardMaterial and really like its rendering feel.\r\n\r\nOn a side note, I have found a tiny bug with the shadowmap: when the light source is in the negative z axis and the shadowmap feeds a custom shader, the shadows are inverted (as seen in this image). The bug maybe located into the packing\/unpacking process, because the shadows look fine when rendered directly.\r\n\r\n![bug_shadowmap](https:\/\/user-images.githubusercontent.com\/11213220\/27600880-9d1fc7d8-5b6d-11e7-8acd-4ba2c45c600d.png)\r\n\r\nAnyways, thank you all for always being on the ball!\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n","created_at":"2017-06-27T17:28:18.000Z","html_url":"https:\/\/github.com\/mrdoob\/three.js\/issues\/11616#issuecomment-311428416","id":311428416,"issue_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/repos\/mrdoob\/three.js\/issues\/11616","node_id":"MDEyOklzc3VlQ29tbWVudDMxMTQyODQxNg==","updated_at":"2017-06-27T17:32:11.000Z","url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/repos\/mrdoob\/three.js\/issues\/comments\/311428416","user":{"following_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/j3zusla\/following{\/other_user}","events_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/j3zusla\/events{\/privacy}","avatar_url":"https:\/\/avatars0.githubusercontent.com\/u\/11213220?v=4","url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/j3zusla","gists_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/j3zusla\/gists{\/gist_id}","html_url":"https:\/\/github.com\/j3zusla","subscriptions_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/j3zusla\/subscriptions","node_id":"MDQ6VXNlcjExMjEzMjIw","repos_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/j3zusla\/repos","received_events_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/j3zusla\/received_events","gravatar_id":"","starred_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/j3zusla\/starred{\/owner}{\/repo}","site_admin":false,"login":"j3zusla","type":"User","id":11213220,"followers_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/j3zusla\/followers","organizations_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/j3zusla\/orgs"}},{"index":4,"author_association":"COLLABORATOR","body":"> if there are multiple light sources, one can easily see that something is not right...\r\n\r\nSorry, I still do not understand what you are referring to.\r\n\r\n>when the light source is in the negative z axis and the shadowmap feeds a custom shader, the shadows are inverted\r\n\r\nSorry, I do not understand what you are referring to.","created_at":"2017-06-27T18:35:20.000Z","html_url":"https:\/\/github.com\/mrdoob\/three.js\/issues\/11616#issuecomment-311446621","id":311446621,"issue_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/repos\/mrdoob\/three.js\/issues\/11616","node_id":"MDEyOklzc3VlQ29tbWVudDMxMTQ0NjYyMQ==","updated_at":"2017-06-27T18:35:20.000Z","url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/repos\/mrdoob\/three.js\/issues\/comments\/311446621","user":{"following_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/WestLangley\/following{\/other_user}","events_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/WestLangley\/events{\/privacy}","avatar_url":"https:\/\/avatars2.githubusercontent.com\/u\/1000017?v=4","url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/WestLangley","gists_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/WestLangley\/gists{\/gist_id}","html_url":"https:\/\/github.com\/WestLangley","subscriptions_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/WestLangley\/subscriptions","node_id":"MDQ6VXNlcjEwMDAwMTc=","repos_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/WestLangley\/repos","received_events_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/WestLangley\/received_events","gravatar_id":"","starred_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/WestLangley\/starred{\/owner}{\/repo}","site_admin":false,"login":"WestLangley","type":"User","id":1000017,"followers_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/WestLangley\/followers","organizations_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/WestLangley\/orgs"}},{"index":5,"author_association":"NONE","body":"> if there are multiple light sources, one can easily see that something is not right...\r\n\r\nLet's say you have a scene that contains a large world. The best option to get a constant light is to use  ambiant lighting, which is the first source of light. Ambiant lights don't cast shadows, therefore a need for  a second source of light to cast shadows (directional light in my case). This second source of light creates the color artifact; the color of the surrounding illuminated area that you mentioned, that does not look natural. Unfortunatly, there are no parameters to remove the artifact caused by this extra light and have proper shadows. \r\n\r\n> when the light source is in the negative z axis and the shadowmap feeds a custom shader, the shadows are inverted\r\n\r\nMaybe, this picture will help you understand better:\r\n\r\n![zaxis_bug_shadowmap_three js](https:\/\/user-images.githubusercontent.com\/11213220\/27607523-6d048248-5b84-11e7-8faa-73fd8a1eb0d6.png)\r\n\r\nhope this helps.\r\n\r\n\r\n","created_at":"2017-06-27T20:09:16.000Z","html_url":"https:\/\/github.com\/mrdoob\/three.js\/issues\/11616#issuecomment-311470616","id":311470616,"issue_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/repos\/mrdoob\/three.js\/issues\/11616","node_id":"MDEyOklzc3VlQ29tbWVudDMxMTQ3MDYxNg==","updated_at":"2017-06-27T20:15:59.000Z","url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/repos\/mrdoob\/three.js\/issues\/comments\/311470616","user":{"following_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/j3zusla\/following{\/other_user}","events_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/j3zusla\/events{\/privacy}","avatar_url":"https:\/\/avatars0.githubusercontent.com\/u\/11213220?v=4","url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/j3zusla","gists_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/j3zusla\/gists{\/gist_id}","html_url":"https:\/\/github.com\/j3zusla","subscriptions_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/j3zusla\/subscriptions","node_id":"MDQ6VXNlcjExMjEzMjIw","repos_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/j3zusla\/repos","received_events_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/j3zusla\/received_events","gravatar_id":"","starred_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/j3zusla\/starred{\/owner}{\/repo}","site_admin":false,"login":"j3zusla","type":"User","id":11213220,"followers_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/j3zusla\/followers","organizations_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/j3zusla\/orgs"}},{"index":6,"author_association":"COLLABORATOR","body":">This second source of light creates the color artifact; the color of the surrounding illuminated area that you mentioned, that does not look natural. Unfortunately, there are no parameters to remove the artifact caused by this extra light.\r\n\r\nIf you add a light source, the illuminated area gets brighter. That is to be expected. I do not see a problem here.\r\n\r\nA shadow map is computed from the point of view of the light source. I do not see a problem here.","created_at":"2017-06-27T20:25:58.000Z","html_url":"https:\/\/github.com\/mrdoob\/three.js\/issues\/11616#issuecomment-311474858","id":311474858,"issue_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/repos\/mrdoob\/three.js\/issues\/11616","node_id":"MDEyOklzc3VlQ29tbWVudDMxMTQ3NDg1OA==","updated_at":"2017-06-27T20:25:58.000Z","url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/repos\/mrdoob\/three.js\/issues\/comments\/311474858","user":{"following_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/WestLangley\/following{\/other_user}","events_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/WestLangley\/events{\/privacy}","avatar_url":"https:\/\/avatars2.githubusercontent.com\/u\/1000017?v=4","url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/WestLangley","gists_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/WestLangley\/gists{\/gist_id}","html_url":"https:\/\/github.com\/WestLangley","subscriptions_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/WestLangley\/subscriptions","node_id":"MDQ6VXNlcjEwMDAwMTc=","repos_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/WestLangley\/repos","received_events_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/WestLangley\/received_events","gravatar_id":"","starred_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/WestLangley\/starred{\/owner}{\/repo}","site_admin":false,"login":"WestLangley","type":"User","id":1000017,"followers_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/WestLangley\/followers","organizations_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/WestLangley\/orgs"}},{"index":7,"author_association":"OWNER","body":"> On a side note, I have found a tiny bug with the shadowmap\r\n\r\nIf there is a bug you should create a new issue for this.","created_at":"2017-06-30T18:08:11.000Z","html_url":"https:\/\/github.com\/mrdoob\/three.js\/issues\/11616#issuecomment-312336139","id":312336139,"issue_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/repos\/mrdoob\/three.js\/issues\/11616","node_id":"MDEyOklzc3VlQ29tbWVudDMxMjMzNjEzOQ==","updated_at":"2017-06-30T18:08:11.000Z","url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/repos\/mrdoob\/three.js\/issues\/comments\/312336139","user":{"following_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/mrdoob\/following{\/other_user}","events_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/mrdoob\/events{\/privacy}","avatar_url":"https:\/\/avatars0.githubusercontent.com\/u\/97088?v=4","url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/mrdoob","gists_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/mrdoob\/gists{\/gist_id}","html_url":"https:\/\/github.com\/mrdoob","subscriptions_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/mrdoob\/subscriptions","node_id":"MDQ6VXNlcjk3MDg4","repos_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/mrdoob\/repos","received_events_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/mrdoob\/received_events","gravatar_id":"","starred_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/mrdoob\/starred{\/owner}{\/repo}","site_admin":false,"login":"mrdoob","type":"User","id":97088,"followers_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/use